cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "llm-gpu-lab: One GPU. Full LLM workflow. Real benchmarks. No cloud required."
message: "If you use this software in your work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Li
    given-names: Daoyuan
    email: lidaoyuan2816@gmail.com
repository-code: "https://github.com/DaoyuanLi2816/llm-gpu-lab"
license: Apache-2.0
keywords:
  - llm
  - gpu
  - pytorch
  - transformers
  - peft
  - lora
  - qlora
  - gguf
  - llama.cpp
abstract: >-
  An educational and engineering reference repository that lets a developer with
  one local consumer NVIDIA GPU (RTX 4080 class, 16 GB) run a complete LLM
  workflow locally: environment diagnosis, tokenizer training, tiny GPT
  pretraining, generation, LoRA / QLoRA SFT, evaluation, GGUF / llama.cpp
  export, GPU benchmarking, and a reproducible HTML report.
